Hero Robb presents
a journey of guilt
fear
and denial.
These are your
 FIRST TIMES.
Open your eyes
> open my eyes
> open my eyes
You are in a large room that looks as though it belongs in the basement of a hospital. A coppery smell seems to grow stronger with every breath. The fluorescent lights cast a dark yellow hue on most of the dirty, dull gray in this room when they aren't flickering off. Your shoes make small ripping sounds as you walk across the sticky tiles. There are several gurneys, piled into a corner. Morgue drawers line three of the four walls, extending up to a ceiling low enough for you to reach. An off-white sheet covers a figure on a gurney in the center of the room. The door on the last wall is covered with a dark brown crust. To get your bearings, you make an arbitrary assumption that the door will lead north.
You can go north.
You aren't sure how you got here or even where you are, but you aren't worried. This must be a dream.
clang...
> x gurneys
> x gurneys
These gurneys are all dirty and a few of them are tipped over. A shiny metal blade protrudes slightly from underneath one that is completely upside down. Why are these here?
> take scalpel
> take scalpel
You carefully slide the metal blade out from underneath the heavy gurney and pick it up. It's a scalpel.
> x covered figure
> x covered figure
A sheet covers a human shaped figure. It seems to have a large lump in it's middle and dark stains have dried on the lower half, where the legs would be. The padding of the gurney seems to have the same brownish stains. Something drips onto the floor. It seems to drip slower and slower. Is it really a person under the sheet?
> take sheet
> take sheet
You slowly pull the sheet from the figure. A life sized wooden doll of a pregnant woman is under it.
> x doll
> x doll
A doll, as large as a real women, lays atop a gurney. She is naked. What seems to be a pinkish tumor is growing out of her stomach, making her seem pregnant. Her green eyes seem to follow you, but that's just a trick of the light.
> use scalpel on tumor
> use scalpel on tumor
With shaking hands, you slide the scalpel across the pink flesh, but either the scalpel is too dull or the tumor is stronger than you had thought because you only scratched it. You drag it across again, harder this time. Blood drains out, rather than squirting. The skin folds to either side and dozens of tiny spiders come crawling out onto the gurney and your hand. Startled, you jump back and brush them off. When you glance back, you see that the spiders have disappeared. They must have squeezed into the drawers or are hiding somewhere. Spider webs are visible inside the tumor.
> take cluster
> take cluster
You try to reach the cluster without touching many of the webs on the way. You find that this is impossible. You quickly shove your hand through halfway to the elbow, grasp the cluster, and jerk your hand out. Still no sign of the mother spider. Peeling back the layers of webbing, you find an alabaster egg.
> x drawer 67
> x drawer 67
Something inside is making that noise. The number plate has actually been removed and "666" has been carved into the door in it's place. There are crudely drawn pictures on this drawer. The first shows a bird and her nest with one egg. The second shows the bird dead and there is a small egg shaped hole punched into the drawer next to her. The final drawing depicts the egg hatching into a snake.
> put egg in hole
> put egg in hole
The pounding immediately stops as the egg slides into the darkness. You can hear it rolling, as if down a long slide or tunnel. Then a sound, like static or  low rumbling, slowly grows louder and louder. You press your ear against the drawer to hear, but the metal grows hot and you pull away. Is there a fire? The door beside you swings open. A sharp and sudden sensation pulls through your stomach and back. This is not a dream.
