> n
This appears to have been a child's playroom. A chest sits in the northeast corner and atop a shelf against the west wall sits a wooden doll the size of a child. Toys clutter the floor, obscuring the once colorful tiles which are now a faded gray. The wallpaper is decorated with smiling clowns. A door stands to the south and another to the east.
You can go south or east.
> open chest
> open chest
You flip the latch up and lift the top of the chest on it's hinges. There seems to be scratches on the inside of the lid, as if someone were trying to claw their way out. Inside it are several inches of dust and a stack of play money.
> take play money
> take play money
As you grab the money, a cloud of dust rises and you back away to avoid breathing it in.
> x toys
> x toys
You look through the plastic toys for a bit before coming across a stuffed bear that seems familiar. The brown plush animal is heavier than you expected and looks up at you with a tired, sad face. As you pick off some of its caked on dirt, you feel a sharp pain in your hand and drop it instinctively. Your finger is bleeding.
> x shelf
> x shelf
The shelves stand about half as tall as you do. You see two childrens books on the shelves, a green book and a red book. Sitting atop the shelf with his legs dangling down the front is a doll the size of a small child, maybe five years old.
> use scalpel on stuffed bear
> use scalpel on stuffed bear
You cut open the bear and remove many needles. The bear is now empty and harmless.
You take both the needles and the stuffed bear.
> x child doll
> x child doll
The doll is about as large as a five or six year old child. He sits upon the shelf, legs dangling down. A scar runs across his breast, starting from his left shoulder and leading to a heart shaped hole in his chest. His arms end not with hands but with tiny holes in the ends of his wrists. Instead of eyes, large holes are gashed into his head.
> read green book
> read green book
Once upon a time, there was a scared little boy.
He was frightened because he lived in a big house all alone.
He never had a mother or father.
Sometimes a monster would come in and try to get him.
Then the monster would leave food for the boy to eat.
The boy was very frightened of being alone and of the monster.
> read red book
> read red book
Deep in the dark place, a woman is crying. She cries because her heart is missing. It was given to another and never seen again. The woman was fooled by gifts and promises. Something safe and soft was given to her and she saw love. She was given something beautiful and something rare before she opened herself and gave up her heart. Now she is alone and sad. So very sad. She can see only darkness, and deep in that dark place, she is crying. She cries because her heart is missing. It was given to another and never seen again. The woman was fooled by gifts and promises. Something safe and soft was given to her and she saw love. She was given something beautiful and something rare before she opened herself and gave up her heart. Now she is alone and sad. So very sad. She can see only darkness, and deep in that dark place, she is crying. She cries because her heart is missing. It was given to another and never seen again. The woman was fooled by gifts and promises. Something safe and soft was given to her and she saw love. She was given something beautiful and something rare before she opened herself and gave up her heart. Now she is alone and sad. So very sad. She can see only darkness, and deep in that dark place, she is crying. She cries because her heart is missing. It was given to another and never seen again. The woman was fooled by gifts and promises. Something safe and soft was given to her and she saw love. She was given something beautiful and something rare before she opened herself and gave up her heart. Now she is alone and sad. So very sad.
It repeats like this over and over for the entire book.
