The room is lit in neon colors, but you can't see where the lights are. You can't even tell if this is indoors or outdoors since all of the walls except the one to the west have been replaced by wire mesh that goes up as high as you can see. The concrete flooring is broken in places and a stage sits quietly in the center of this "room" with mismatched seating encircling it. An empty bar begs for customers in the south side. Curtains adorn the wire fence to the east.
