> use play money on vending machine
> use play money on vending machine
The machine readily takes the money. There is a whirring and grinding from within before the crash of what you have paid for fell into reach. You open the flap at the bottom of the vending machine and remove an unmarked silver can.
> use can opener on can
> use can opener on can
You put the can on the floor, attatch the can opener, and twist the handle until you have almost cut the entire lid off. Then you bend the top open and empty the can on the floor. A pair of gemmed earrings were inside.
> s
> s
This door looks as though it belongs in the maternity ward. There is a seat with stirrups for the patient's legs once sat in the center of the room, but it has been cast aside and now sits awkwardly on the floor around various bits of floor and wall that must have fallen when it was tossed. In it's place is a snake sculpture that stands upright nearly touching the ceiling.
You can go north.
> x snake sculpture
> x snake sculpture
Protruding through the broken tiling where the birthing seat once was are several hands, roughly chiseled from gray stone. The snake that rises up from them has been sculpted with incredible detail in comparison. It's head almost brushes the ceiling and it's mouth is open wide. You approach it in awe. Each scale, fang, and even the eyes have their texture cut and imprinted very sharply with clear reverance, but you have a difficult time seeing the top as it is much taller than you. You hear a low, growling sound and freeze with fear as you swear the snake god is leaning down to you. Tiling gives way and the serpent crashes down, strangely silent, as you back away in horror. The silence of the fall is more unnerving than the threat of being crushed. The sculpture rests uneasily in the floor, with barely more than it's head visible. You approach it again, very tentatively and careful of where you step. The hole doesn't seem to have opened any more of the floor and you wonder how it was supported in the first place. As you look down upon the snake's head, you see something moving inside it's mouth. Kneeling, you see that the fangs are slowly producing a transparent, slightly red fluid. It drips slowly onto the forked tongue and down the statue's throat.
> take kiss key
> take kiss key
As you grab the token from amidst the rubble, you realize it is connected via a tiny chain to a key.
