> use kiss key on north door
> use kiss key on north door
The key fits into the lock and turns, although it requires quite a lot more force than you expected. The lock must have countless years of rust built up inside. After you finally unlock the door, you open it and enter the room.
The lights don't seem to work properly here, you can only see from the residual light coming through the threshold. The first thing you notice is an odd stench. It isn't horrible, but very powerful. And it reminds you of...death? This is a circular room, with counters, sinks, and a two way mirror on the walls surrounding an operating table. The doll from the morgue is here, but how? There is no trace of her tumor, but she has been cut apart at the waist and there is no sign of her lower half. She sits erect upon her split hips on the operating table. The table seems to glisten about her. The lights flicker on and mercilessly don't go dark again. The operating table is wet with blood. Partially detatched from her body are organs, some ruptured, some disected, and some whole, scattered across the table. You feel a wet crunch under your shoe and you feel intensely ill.
You can go south.
> x doll
> x doll
The naked and brutalized doll has her head lowered with both arms crossed over her chest. Her skin seems to be different in different places. Some patches are wooden, as before, and some are soft and have the look of real flesh.
> use flowers on altar
> use flowers on altar
You decide to put the flowers on the blood stained altar. You feel silly and are about to take the flowers back when you realize the doll is now looking straight into your eyes. Startled, you slip on the slick blood and fall to the floor. You stand up, blood dripping from your hands, and expect to see the doll's face cast down again. She still stares directly at you, a slight smile on her face.
> use earrings on altar
> use earrings on altar
You place the earrings on the wet altar, never taking your eyes off of the doll. One of her arms opens to her side. Something is wrong with the center of her chest. It looks as though there is another injury she was hiding.
> use stuffed bear on altar
> use stuffed bear on altar
You place the teddy bear on the bloody altar and the remaining arm opens, revealing her naked breasts. Your suspicions are confirmed as blood trickles down her flesh from the incision across her sternum and her ribs are pulled apart. Inside her chest cavity is a red wooden heart.
> take red heart
> take red heart
You reach into the warm, moist insides and grip the heart, never taking your eyes off of the doll. Her gaze never leaves yours. You pull the red heart from her.
Something is wrong. You need to leave.
Now.

The lights go out. You can't see your hand in front of your face. Your breathing is becoming hard to control.
Calm down.
Find a way to light up the hallway so you can see.

What's that? Is that the doll's voice? You can't get her wide staring eyes out of your mind's eye.

"I'll never leave you," the voice calls out and laughs. Was it closer?
Maybe you should go the other way...

The doll's voice echoes, "You've made me so happy." It's definitely getting closer.

The laugh is coming from right behind you. RUN!

"FOREVER!" the doll's voice screams and the gray of the hallway seems almost luminous as the fluorescent lights are burning brightly once again. You are alone.
