A corridor unfolds in front of you to the east, very slim without much room to maneuver.
You hear footsteps behind you and see at least 3 people with smoothe, featureless skin instead of faces approach you.
You dart further east to avoid the faceless people.

A circle of chairs takes up much of the room, in the middle is another chair. The corridor is tighter than before, leading east.
The faceless creatures are still close behind, reaching ever closer.
One of the creatures almost grabs you. You manage to elude them and run east.

The corridor ends here. You can go down through a hole in the floor. A child is tied to a radiator with rope, clutching a toy tower. He looks at you with pleading eyes, but makes not a sound.
The monsters are so close they could touch you. You've got to get out of here.
