> x left side
> x left side

Looking over the banister, you see a subway. A woman with green eyes sits alone on a bench, reading a book as she waits for the next train to come to a stop. The doors open and she approaches it and walks inside. She sits alone as the rumbling train begins to shoot down the tunnels. No, she isn't alone. A life sized doll of a man sits on the train, as well. This doll is different from any of the others you have seen. It has no scars or missing parts. It simply stares forward with a blank expression. She looks toward it and smiles. The vibration of the journey jostles the doll ever so slightly.
"Say hello," you whisper.
> x right side
> x right side

You see a kitchen. A green eyed woman is eating at a dinner table across from the scarless life sized doll. She wears an elegant emerald dress that puts emphasis on her brilliant eyes. She seems to be permanently attempting a smile, but never quite reaching her goal.
"Do you want to go out tonight? Maybe..." she says without lifting her eyes from her plate. "...maybe catch a movie or...or something?"
The doll looks directly ahead. Never moving. Never speaking.
"We could..." she starts, but never finishes. The woman stands and begins to put the dishes into the sink.
"Say yes," you whisper. "Please, say yes."
> down
> down
You walk further down the stairs. The desire to look over both sides is overwhelming once again.
You can go down.
