You can't see anything on this side of the staircase. You lean slightly over the edge and can hear voices.
"...be serious? Do you know how this sadistic piece of shit killed the Smithson's? Did you hear what he said to their family at the trial? And now you're going to let the son of a bitch say something here, too?"
"It's not special treatment, Harry. Everyone can say something at the end. Nothing's stopping him from screaming right now, and he just gave himself up. That has to mean something, right?"
"I think he just wants to die. And I still say that fucker don't deserve regular treatment. Not after what he's done."
You can see something in the darkness now. A man appears, wearing an orange jumpsuit. A scar is slightly visible under his collar on the left side. He opens his mouth to speak and stares directly into your eyes.
"It was your fault."
> x right side
> x right side
A pudgy middle aged man pushes a lawnmower across his yard, breathing without rhythm. He stops for a moment to wipe the sticky moisture from his forehead and lean slightly on the mower. As he wipes his moustache on his sleeve, two children approach him.
"Dad, tell Adam that old house isn't haunted." He points without looking to a dillapidated house on a street corner a block away.
"I never said it was haunted!"
"You said that an old demon lives there!"
"That's not haunted! Haunted means ghosts!"
The father holds up a hand and half heartedly shakes it, still breathing oddly. "There no ghosts or demons. Not there. Or here." He lazily points to the ground and then makes a sweeping gesture. "Or anywhere. You stay away from that place, though. Ok?"
Adam chips in his thoughts "My mom said a psycho killer grew up there and now a demon lives there."
"Shut up, Adam." the other little boy says while looking up at his father before walking away. The man takes another few seconds for himself before fanning his face with the front of his shirt and starting the lawnmower again.
> down
> down
The stairs end here. A mirror stands before you.
> x mirror
> x mirror

You gaze into the mirror and see the man the doll has become. You have broken the apathetic shell. You have torn the flesh open to create your voice and now you see what you have become.
Beautiful.
Nothing is more beautiful than matter and energy recreating itself. You are bleeding from your wounds, the scars will never heal, and you have destroyed all that you loved. But you are not broken. You will not become broken. You will not allow it. Regret is the way forward. Mistakes leave wounds that bleed into the future, and you avoid the recurring pain.
The cosmos explodes in a display of everything. For itself. For you. You are the piece of the universe that, by astronomical luck, is capable of experiencing itself. You feel the universe, content in the pure experience of simply being. You are all things. And all at once.
A
thousand
millennia
pass
and you see your wife and your child. You know this is but a single moment, but it, like all moments, will echo into eternity.
You embrace them.

You have achieved the Apocatastasis ending.
